00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:21,735
Carlo, you pay 25% of your
endorsements to SMI. I'll take 18%.

234
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:25,801
I don't know if it was drugs,
but the guy freaked out.

235
00:23:26,009 --> 00:23:29,868
He's not the guy for you.
How's your mom?

236
00:23:30,077 --> 00:23:33,205
I'm gonna make this easy for you.

237
00:23:33,413 --> 00:23:39,774
What does your heart tell you?
I'm sorry to hear that.

238
00:23:45,092 --> 00:23:49,889
- What's going on?
- They've fired Jerry Maguire.

239
00:23:58,544 --> 00:24:01,464
That's a mistake.

240
00:24:01,569 --> 00:24:05,739
I'm concerned about your family
and your future.

241
00:24:05,843 --> 00:24:09,180
I go back a long way with SMI.

242
00:24:09,388 --> 00:24:12,205
Is Maguire black?

243
00:24:12,413 --> 00:24:17,314
Bob Sugar?
He's... entertaining, funny...

244
00:24:17,419 --> 00:24:20,860
I'm Mr. Black People!

245
00:24:21,068 --> 00:24:24,405
Don't make this harder than it is.

246
00:24:24,613 --> 00:24:28,681
I've got to be honest,
this is very distressing for me.

247
00:24:28,889 --> 00:24:34,103
Remember that stripper
at Laguna Beach? Her name was April.

248
00:24:34,207 --> 00:24:38,796
I remember things.
It's not the money. I do it for you.

249
00:24:39,004 --> 00:24:43,383
- I'm still holding for Katarina.
- I'm talking big money.

250
00:24:43,592 --> 00:24:46,094
Great!

251
00:24:46,199 --> 00:24:50,683
Are you in or out?
This is business not friendship.

252
00:24:50,787 --> 00:24:54,436
You are in... that's good.

253
00:24:54,646 --> 00:24:57,983
I want to cry
for what they did to you.

254
00:24:58,191 --> 00:25:03,509
If it wasn't for the Acura deal,
you know I'd go with you.

255
00:25:03,718 --> 00:25:09,140
Jerry. Oh, God!

256
00:25:09,349 --> 00:25:14,146
Call waiting.
Who could be calling me now?

257
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:18,212
- Hi, Kathy Sanders.
- Still me, Kathy.

258
00:25:20,298 --> 00:25:26,033
Kathy, why are you crying?
Oh... so you're in.

259
00:25:26,241 --> 00:25:29,266
Rod, it's Jerry Maguire.

260
00:25:29,475 --> 00:25:32,707
Jerry Maguire! How am I doing?

261
00:25:32,915 --> 00:25:37,191
I'll tell you. I'm sweating.
Where's my contract?

262
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:41,153
Bob Sugar says
I'm missing out being with you.

263
00:25:41,362 --> 00:25:45,533
- You hear what I'm saying?
- That's why I called.

264
00:25:45,742 --> 00:25:50,017
No, no... Do you truly
hear what I'm saying?

265
00:25:50,121 --> 00:25:54,709
- I hear you, Dad.
- We have to get together.

266
00:25:54,918 --> 00:25:59,819
- Hold on a minute, Rod.
- Personal attention.

267
00:25:59,923 --> 00:26:06,285
- That's what you told my wife.
- That's what I said.

268
00:26:06,493 --> 00:26:11,603
Good! We're just getting started
on the things you need to know.

269
00:26:11,707 --> 00:26:14,523
I will kill for you.

270
00:26:14,731 --> 00:26:20,466
I am a valuable commodity. There's
dudes out there trying to kill me.

271
00:26:20,570 --> 00:26:26,514
I still catch the ball. Touchdown!
I make miracles happen.

272
00:26:26,618 --> 00:26:28,704
Are you in?

273
00:26:28,912 --> 00:26:32,458
I'm from Arizona.
I broke Arizona records.

274
00:26:32,562 --> 00:26:35,899
I went to Arizona State!

275
00:26:36,108 --> 00:26:39,862
- And now you want Arizona dollars.
- Exactly.

276
00:26:40,070 --> 00:26:44,658
I'm sitting here
with an ant problem.

277
00:26:44,763 --> 00:26:50,498
My brother Tee Pee's room
is flooded.

278
00:26:50,602 --> 00:26:53,939
- Say hello to Jerry Maguire.
- Hello.

279
00:26:54,148 --> 00:26:57,172
Hello, Tee Pee.

280
00:26:57,276 --> 00:27:04,575
No one's looking out for me.
I'm supposed to be a superstar.

281
00:27:04,785 --> 00:27:11,145
- Are you in or out?
- You stay with Bob Sugar!

282
00:27:11,249 --> 00:27:15,838
I am a role model.
I have a family to support!

283
00:27:16,046 --> 00:27:19,070
I want a contract in Arizona.

284
00:27:19,279 --> 00:27:22,094
I like you.

285
00:27:22,303 --> 00:27:26,370
My wife likes you.
You're good to my wife.

286
00:27:26,578 --> 00:27:29,811
- I will stay with you.
- That's great.

287
00:27:30,019 --> 00:27:34,608
That's what I'm gonna do for you.
God bless you, Jerry.

288
00:27:34,816 --> 00:27:38,674
This is what you're gonna do for me.

289
00:27:38,882 --> 00:27:42,637
What can I do for you?
You just tell me.

290
00:27:42,846 --> 00:27:48,476
It's personal and very important.
Hell! It's a family motto.

291
00:27:48,685 --> 00:27:52,438
- Are you ready, Jerry?
- I'm ready.

292
00:27:52,648 --> 00:27:55,672
Here it is.

293
00:27:56,506 --> 00:27:59,634
Show me the money.

294
00:27:59,842 --> 00:28:01,824
Show...

295
00:28:02,032 --> 00:28:05,787
...me ...the...

296
00:28:05,995 --> 00:28:08,498
...money... !

297
00:28:08,707 --> 00:28:14,859
- Say it with me, Jerry.
- Show you the money.

298
00:28:15,067 --> 00:28:18,300
No, you can do better than that.

299
00:28:18,508 --> 00:28:22,575
- Bob Sugar's on the other line.
- Show you the money.

300
00:28:22,784 --> 00:28:26,120
- No, show me the money.
- Show me the money.

301
00:28:26,329 --> 00:28:29,457
- Louder!
- Show me the money.

302
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:35,297
- You've got to yell that shit!
- Show me the money!

303
00:28:35,506 --> 00:28:39,364
- Louder, Jerry.
- Show me the moneyl

304
00:28:39,468 --> 00:28:43,223
Show me the money!

305
00:28:43,431 --> 00:28:48,541
- You love this black man.
- I love the black man!

306
00:28:48,645 --> 00:28:53,650
- I love black people.
- I love black people.

307
00:28:53,859 --> 00:28:59,281
Show me the money!

308
00:29:00,115 --> 00:29:03,452
Congratulations,
you're still my agent.

309
00:29:33,485 --> 00:29:38,907
Well... don't worry.

310
00:29:39,011 --> 00:29:44,016
I'm not gonna do
what you think I'm gonna do.

311
00:29:48,708 --> 00:29:51,941
Let me just say...

312
00:29:52,046 --> 00:29:56,946
...as I ease out of the office
I helped build...

313
00:29:57,155 --> 00:30:04,037
I'm sorry, but it's a fact that
there's such a thing... as manners.

314
00:30:06,123 --> 00:30:09,147
A way of treating people.

315
00:30:10,712 --> 00:30:15,820
These fish have manners.

316
00:30:16,030 --> 00:30:22,495
In fact, I'm starting a new company
and the fish will come with me.

317
00:30:22,703 --> 00:30:28,438
Call me sentimental,
but the fish are coming with me.

318
00:30:39,074 --> 00:30:42,307
Okay.

319
00:30:43,767 --> 00:30:48,147
If anybody else
wants to come with me, -

320
00:30:48,251 --> 00:30:54,612
- this is a chance for something
real, and fun, and inspiring -

321
00:30:54,716 --> 00:31:00,660
- in this godforsaken business,
and we will do it together.

322
00:31:02,954 --> 00:31:08,168
Who's coming with me?

323
00:31:08,272 --> 00:31:11,714
Who's coming with me?

324
00:31:14,112 --> 00:31:17,866
Who's coming with me
besides Flipper here?

325
00:31:24,331 --> 00:31:28,398
This is embarrassing.

326
00:31:31,631 --> 00:31:37,157
All right.
Wendy, shall we?

327
00:31:37,366 --> 00:31:41,954
I'm three months away
from the pay increase...

328
00:31:47,794 --> 00:31:51,652
Okay.

329
00:31:59,055 --> 00:32:04,478
- I will go with you.
- Dorothy Boyd, thank you.

330
00:32:12,194 --> 00:32:15,741
Right now?

331
00:32:16,783 --> 00:32:20,850
Don't do it.

332
00:32:24,708 --> 00:32:27,732
Bye.

333
00:32:35,553 --> 00:32:39,620
We'll see you all again.
Sleep tight.

334
00:32:41,809 --> 00:32:45,459
Let's see how they do without us.

335
00:32:56,825 --> 00:33:00,475
Thank you.

336
00:33:00,580 --> 00:33:05,793
- You will have a medical program?
- Oh, sure.

337
00:33:07,462 --> 00:33:10,590
I don't know...

338
00:33:10,694 --> 00:33:16,012
Don't panic.
We're gonna be okay.

339
00:33:16,117 --> 00:33:21,643
We're gonna be great.
We're gonna be... great.

340
00:33:53,762 --> 00:33:58,975
- I wonder what he said.
- My aunt is hearing impaired.

341
00:33:59,184 --> 00:34:04,084
He just said,
"You complete me".

342
00:34:23,585 --> 00:34:30,154
To support one another,
we've got to listen to one another.

343
00:34:30,258 --> 00:34:35,993
Women are taught not to see
each other as good people.

344
00:34:36,097 --> 00:34:40,477
We see each other as enemies.
We compete over men.

345
00:34:40,686 --> 00:34:45,691
- It's true, It's terrible.
- I used to hate women.

346
00:34:45,796 --> 00:34:50,071
Now I've met you guys,
and you're like me.

347
00:34:50,176 --> 00:34:54,138
It's important
because you can be my friends.

348
00:34:54,346 --> 00:34:57,788
- What about medical?
- Of course.

349
00:34:57,892 --> 00:35:01,020
Single parents can't be frivolous.

350
00:35:01,229 --> 00:35:05,922
If you had read what he wrote,
you'd have left, too.

351
00:35:06,026 --> 00:35:12,282
Do you know those child exams
cost $150, and that's if he's well.

352
00:35:12,491 --> 00:35:16,245
- Where is Ray?
- Asleep in the living room.

353
00:35:16,349 --> 00:35:23,127
Don't leave my little boy alone
with your divorced women's group.

354
00:35:23,335 --> 00:35:27,820
I've finally got in touch
with my anger.

355
00:35:36,474 --> 00:35:39,811
What did I do?

356
00:35:40,021 --> 00:35:44,087
Function, function...
Forward motion is everything.

357
00:35:44,295 --> 00:35:46,798
Cush saves all.

358
00:35:46,798 --> 00:35:51,178
Go to Texas. Keep one star,
and they'll all follow.

359
00:35:51,387 --> 00:35:56,496
There's no real loyalty.
You told me that yourself.

360
00:35:56,705 --> 00:36:00,667
- I was trying to sleep with you.
- Well, it worked.

361
00:36:00,875 --> 00:36:06,716
I will not let you fail.
You are Jerry Maguire!

362
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:10,886
King of the house calls.
Master of the living room.

363
00:36:10,990 --> 00:36:15,892
- Okay, this is working.
- You are not a loser.

364
00:36:18,499 --> 00:36:24,651
- Who mentioned losing?
- Wrong word! When can you leave?

365
00:36:52,285 --> 00:36:57,082
- Matt?
- I'm in the back, Jerry.

366
00:36:57,290 --> 00:37:00,418
Would you like a bloody beer?

367
00:37:00,627 --> 00:37:05,007
- Beer and tomato juice.
- I'm fine.

368
00:37:05,215 --> 00:37:10,534
We've spent a lot of time together,
and you know I care about your son.

369
00:37:10,742 --> 00:37:14,704
I'm concerned
that if you stay with SMI...

370
00:37:14,913 --> 00:37:18,771
We've decided to stay with you.

371
00:37:23,985 --> 00:37:29,825
I'm not really a hugger.
I can't let go.

372
00:37:30,033 --> 00:37:35,664
I told myself if he shows up,
we stick with him.

373
00:37:35,768 --> 00:37:40,148
- Hey, Jerry. How's it going?
- Hey, Cush.

374
00:37:40,357 --> 00:37:45,049
- How are you?
- You remember Keith.

375
00:37:45,258 --> 00:37:49,950
He must go number one in the draft,
and I want him to play.

376
00:37:50,054 --> 00:37:53,600
It'll either be Denver or San Diego.

377
00:37:53,809 --> 00:37:59,856
- I'll either surf or ski.
- Denver's where he should be.

378
00:38:00,065 --> 00:38:06,635
You know I don't do contracts,
but what you do have ls my word.

379
00:38:06,739 --> 00:38:11,014
And it's stronger than oak.

380
00:39:00,025 --> 00:39:03,153
- Hello.
- Jerry Maguire.

381
00:39:03,257 --> 00:39:08,054
- Is Avery there?
- She has an NFL meeting in Atlanta.

382
00:39:10,870 --> 00:39:17,439
- Hello?
- My son's here with the nanny.

383
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:22,444
- In our office?
- Nanny? I prefer child technician.

384
00:39:22,653 --> 00:39:30,161
- I came home to work here.
- Fine. Dorothy, we are backl

385
00:39:30,265 --> 00:39:35,896
We are so very, very back.
I resigned Cush. We're set.

386
00:39:36,104 --> 00:39:40,797
- I am so happy for you.
- Happy for us.

387
00:39:41,006 --> 00:39:43,091
Happy for us.

388
00:39:43,300 --> 00:39:50,391
Rod, being at the draft will help.
Get on the plane and meet us there.

389
00:39:50,495 --> 00:39:53,623
Good. See you there.

390
00:39:53,728 --> 00:39:57,377
Avery will be at the B-gate at 4:15.

391
00:39:57,481 --> 00:40:02,174
Do you know the human head
weighs eight pounds?

392
00:40:02,382 --> 00:40:08,431
Troy Aikman, in only six years,
has passed for 16,303 yards.

393
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:16,356
- Bees and dogs can smell fear.
- I've booked Tidwell at the Mariot.

394
00:40:16,565 --> 00:40:22,300
Pete Rose made 4,256 hits and
he's not in the Hall of Fame.

395
00:40:22,509 --> 00:40:27,827
Did you know that my neighbour
has three rabbits?

396
00:40:28,035 --> 00:40:31,789
I can't compete with that.

397
00:40:31,893 --> 00:40:35,022
- Did we go over everything?
- Yep.

398
00:40:35,231 --> 00:40:39,505
- Back on Tuesday, right?
- Yeah.

399
00:40:40,757 --> 00:40:45,345
- Ray, wish me luck.
- Good luck!

400
00:41:05,158 --> 00:41:09,330
- Hey, Rod, you made it.
- Jerry...

401
00:41:10,268 --> 00:41:16,524
- Hi, Cush.
- We should be selling these.

402
00:41:16,628 --> 00:41:21,842
This is my agent, you might
want to get his autograph.

403
00:41:22,051 --> 00:41:26,326
- Excuse me...
- Are you Hootie?

404
00:41:26,535 --> 00:41:31,957
No, I'm not Hootie.

405
00:41:36,337 --> 00:41:39,778
Is it gonna be San Diego or Denver?

406
00:41:45,722 --> 00:41:49,476
He'll either surf or ski.

407
00:41:55,316 --> 00:41:59,486
Rod, at last I find you.

408
00:41:59,695 --> 00:42:03,762
What am I doing here, Jerry?
This ain't my party.

409
00:42:03,866 --> 00:42:09,184
- Nobody gives a damn about me.
- Let's walk through the lobby.

410
00:42:09,289 --> 00:42:14,711
I want the media and the reps
to see you for what you are:

411
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:19,195
The best-kept secret in the NFL.

412
00:42:19,404 --> 00:42:24,201
You are the wide - receiver.
You're fast, fierce and charismatic.

413
00:42:24,409 --> 00:42:27,225
You are the man! Ready?

414
00:42:27,433 --> 00:42:34,420
Let's go. The fiercest.
You are the man.

415
00:42:34,629 --> 00:42:39,320
- Let's do it.
- Hi, Mel. Hi, Tom.

416
00:42:39,529 --> 00:42:44,847
It's a good thing you were able
to hold onto Cushman.

417
00:42:44,952 --> 00:42:50,479
I want you to meet Rod Tidwell,
110 catches, 1,550 yards last year.

418
00:43:24,473 --> 00:43:28,853
I came all that way
just to walk the lobby.

419
00:43:29,061 --> 00:43:34,692
- It might have even worked, too.
- Yeah? Let's do it again.

420
00:43:36,152 --> 00:43:41,470
See the Reebok-ad down there.
Where are my endorsements?

421
00:43:41,575 --> 00:43:46,163
No love from Chevy,
no love from Pepsi...

422
00:43:46,372 --> 00:43:50,021
I ain't gettin' no love from Nike.

423
00:43:50,229 --> 00:43:54,505
Did I ever tell you
about my Reebok story?

424
00:43:54,714 --> 00:43:59,928
- I've got to get back to Cushman.
- Oh, your golden paycheck.

425
00:44:00,136 --> 00:44:04,620
I'll boil it down for you.
Fuck Reebok!

426
00:44:04,829 --> 00:44:09,833
All they do is ignore me.
Always have.

427
00:44:09,939 --> 00:44:17,341
For a moment down there,
you got that chip off your shoulder.

428
00:44:17,446 --> 00:44:22,868
You let people in.
You were brilliant.

429
00:44:24,016 --> 00:44:26,727
- Really?
- Brilliant.

430
00:44:26,935 --> 00:44:30,897
- See you tomorrow.
- You're loving me now.

431
00:44:31,107 --> 00:44:34,131
I'm showing you the money!

432
00:44:34,235 --> 00:44:41,221
I was just testing you, but to hear
you say that makes me love you.

433
00:44:41,325 --> 00:44:45,705
Jerry, come back.

434
00:44:45,914 --> 00:44:49,042
- How was your flight?
- Good.

435
00:44:49,146 --> 00:44:56,237
If you can find your size, grab
some of those shoes by the door.

436
00:45:02,389 --> 00:45:06,874
Cush, Matt,
we have a decision to make.

437
00:45:07,082 --> 00:45:12,400
San Diego just came in with
a last-minute scenario. It's big.

438
00:45:12,505 --> 00:45:18,344
- He's got to go number one.
- San Diego wants him bad.

439
00:45:18,448 --> 00:45:23,766
- What happened to Denver?
- Before a draft, people get crazy.

440
00:45:23,871 --> 00:45:30,232
San Diego is offering seven years
for 30. Signing bonus of 8.

441
00:45:30,441 --> 00:45:34,403
- Should I unplug the phone?
- Damn reporters.

442
00:45:34,611 --> 00:45:37,845
You just say, "No comment".

443
00:45:38,053 --> 00:45:41,807
I'm no good at
talking and saying nothing.

444
00:45:42,015 --> 00:45:44,935
Let me.

445
00:45:45,665 --> 00:45:50,149
For you, it's a pleasure.
This is Cush.

446
00:45:50,357 --> 00:45:55,363
It's Sugar. Is Maguire there?
Sniff if he is.

447
00:45:55,571 --> 00:46:03,288
You're in with the big boys now.
I got you the deal you needed.

448
00:46:03,392 --> 00:46:09,649
This is business, not friendship.
You've got to be strong.

449
00:46:09,858 --> 00:46:13,820
Okay, buddy? See you later.

450
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:21,536
No comment.

451
00:46:26,438 --> 00:46:29,670
- He's got it all wrong.
- You're on TV again.

452
00:46:29,878 --> 00:46:32,694
I'm sick of me.

453
00:46:44,374 --> 00:46:49,483
Before I go back to Denver,
let's put something down on paper.

454
00:46:49,692 --> 00:46:56,052
- A contract with Jerry Maguire.
- Not right now, Jerry.

455
00:47:00,849 --> 00:47:05,855
Do I know everything
there is to know here, Matt?

456
00:47:08,045 --> 00:47:11,173
You're not talklng with Bob Sugar?

457
00:47:11,381 --> 00:47:19,307
- Denver would only deal with him.
- Said who? Sugar?

458
00:47:19,411 --> 00:47:26,292
- I'm learning as I go here.
- You let him deal behind my back?

459
00:47:26,502 --> 00:47:32,446
I'm sorry... I love my son.

460
00:47:32,654 --> 00:47:39,223
I love your son!
I brought Denver to 20 million.

461
00:47:39,432 --> 00:47:44,333
You listened to Bob Sugar?
That is a child.

462
00:47:44,437 --> 00:47:48,921
You let that snake in the door?

463
00:47:49,755 --> 00:47:56,638
Okay, listen, rookie mistake.
I'll fix this Denver thing for you.

464
00:47:56,846 --> 00:48:01,539
You didn't sign anything
with Sugar, right?

465
00:48:01,748 --> 00:48:06,545
Matt...?
Tell me you didn't sign.

