686
01:11:05,408 --> 01:11:10,831
- Yeah, what happened there?
- This is a working relationship.

687
01:11:11,039 --> 01:11:13,438
Exactly.

688
01:11:13,646 --> 01:11:19,485
The other night I was lonely.
I felt you understood something.

689
01:11:19,694 --> 01:11:26,577
We've got a company to think about,
and I'll never try that again.

690
01:11:26,681 --> 01:11:32,416
You walked out on a job for me...
Can this be right?

691
01:11:32,625 --> 01:11:35,961
Exactly.

692
01:11:36,170 --> 01:11:41,488
I know right now you need
to be alone with your thoughts.

693
01:11:41,696 --> 01:11:46,493
Find out what's gone wrong
and fix it .. . alone.

694
01:11:46,702 --> 01:11:52,646
Alone! Alone, alone.

695
01:11:54,314 --> 01:11:58,173
- You want to go out to dinner?
- Great!

696
01:11:58,277 --> 01:12:03,387
I broke up with that loser,
and then he started stalking me.

697
01:12:03,595 --> 01:12:11,520
- What do you mean by stalking?
- Coming over uninvited.

698
01:12:23,512 --> 01:12:26,953
Excuse me... Ladies.

699
01:12:27,162 --> 01:12:32,167
Good evening,
I'm looking for Dorothy Boyd.

700
01:12:32,376 --> 01:12:38,111
- She's in the kitchen.
- Laurel... Hello.

701
01:12:38,320 --> 01:12:42,908
- Where are you taking her tonight?
- You're the nanny?

702
01:12:43,117 --> 01:12:46,245
- Au pair.
- Au pair?

703
01:12:47,704 --> 01:12:50,728
Jerry!

704
01:12:51,876 --> 01:12:54,795
He likes you.

705
01:12:55,004 --> 01:13:02,304
Ray, I've got some gifts for you.
Do you like presents?

706
01:13:02,512 --> 01:13:07,413
Arizona Cardinals.
It's the team Rod plays for.

707
01:13:07,518 --> 01:13:12,523
- Is that your laundry?
- Would you like a Steelers hat?

708
01:13:12,627 --> 01:13:17,737
- I've got it in grey, too.
- Thanks, Jerry.

709
01:13:17,945 --> 01:13:23,576
And I've got an energy bar.
This will keep you up all night.

710
01:13:23,785 --> 01:13:28,165
That's not a good idea.
I'll take that.

711
01:13:29,728 --> 01:13:34,629
Hey, it looks like you've got a fan.

712
01:13:35,776 --> 01:13:39,948
That's more than a dress,
that's an Audrey Hepburn movie.

713
01:13:40,052 --> 01:13:45,995
I got a bit revved up at the thought
of an evening among adults.

714
01:13:46,204 --> 01:13:51,105
- Jerry, Chad. Chad, Jerry.
- Yeah... Am I dressed okay?

715
01:13:55,172 --> 01:14:02,471
- Don't let him stay up too late.
- Tonight he'll learn about jazz.

716
01:14:02,681 --> 01:14:06,434
Good,
that'll put him to sleep early.

717
01:14:06,643 --> 01:14:09,354
I want to go too.

718
01:14:09,562 --> 01:14:14,464
No, you stay here with Chad
and be good. Kiss me.

719
01:14:14,672 --> 01:14:17,592
Let's go.

720
01:14:18,948 --> 01:14:22,701
- Good night.
- Give me a hug.

721
01:15:04,830 --> 01:15:10,356
- I'll meet you at the car.
- You forgot your keys.

722
01:15:10,565 --> 01:15:14,632
Ray kissed him just like a dad!

723
01:15:14,841 --> 01:15:19,638
Wasn't that thrilling?
He must have been needing that.

724
01:15:19,846 --> 01:15:25,268
Don't cry at the start of a date,
just cry at the end, like I do.

725
01:15:25,373 --> 01:15:28,709
Don't be a shoulder
for him to cry on, either.

726
01:15:28,814 --> 01:15:34,861
Keys.
Oh dear...

727
01:16:00,306 --> 01:16:07,083
Ever since you've met me,
I've been...

728
01:16:08,960 --> 01:16:13,340
It was laziness,
my breakup with Avery.

729
01:16:13,549 --> 01:16:18,554
It doesn't just happen.
Somebody is always to blame.

730
01:16:18,659 --> 01:16:22,725
You work at it
like you do a job.

731
01:16:22,829 --> 01:16:28,251
Maybe,
love shouldn't be such hard work.

732
01:16:28,460 --> 01:16:31,381
Yeah, maybe so.

733
01:16:31,589 --> 01:16:36,803
But it's not every day you say
goodbye to a woman like that.

734
01:16:38,784 --> 01:16:42,017
A song for the lovers?

735
01:16:42,225 --> 01:16:48,482
- No, no, we work together.
- This is like an office meeting.

736
01:16:48,690 --> 01:16:51,506
I know what you mean.

737
01:16:51,610 --> 01:16:58,493
It wasn't like my marriage to Roger
was any good, even before ...

738
01:16:58,701 --> 01:17:01,829
Before...?

739
01:17:02,663 --> 01:17:08,294
Jerry...
Let's not tell our sad stories.

740
01:17:13,299 --> 01:17:17,158
I'll be back in just a second, okay?

741
01:17:46,773 --> 01:17:50,318
They sting.
Let Chad catch the bee in the glass.

742
01:17:50,422 --> 01:17:55,532
He won't hurt him.
You've got such a good heart.

743
01:18:23,687 --> 01:18:30,152
- Well, this would be goodnight.
- Goodnight.

744
01:18:30,361 --> 01:18:35,366
I'll see you tomorrow.
It's a big day.

745
01:18:59,558 --> 01:19:03,730
- Well, goodnight.
- Goodnight.

746
01:19:41,687 --> 01:19:47,005
- Let me fix this.
- Good idea.

747
01:20:40,082 --> 01:20:44,045
I think you should not come in.

748
01:20:44,150 --> 01:20:48,841
Or... come in.

749
01:20:49,051 --> 01:20:54,369
- Depending on how you feel.
- The same to you.

750
01:20:54,473 --> 01:21:01,980
No, I have to go in.
I live here.

751
01:21:10,114 --> 01:21:13,660
Right.

752
01:21:16,163 --> 01:21:20,021
I'll come in.

753
01:21:20,229 --> 01:21:23,462
Good.

754
01:21:30,761 --> 01:21:34,412
Are you sure we want to do this?

755
01:21:37,435 --> 01:21:39,625
Hell, yes!

756
01:21:49,218 --> 01:21:52,869
- Did he have a good night?
- Yeah, he's asleep.

757
01:21:52,973 --> 01:21:58,187
- How did it go with sport-boy?
- Still going.

758
01:21:58,395 --> 01:22:00,480
All right.

759
01:22:04,235 --> 01:22:07,571
Chad... how are you?

760
01:22:09,866 --> 01:22:13,515
- Treat her right.
- Yeah...

761
01:22:15,705 --> 01:22:18,625
She's great.

762
01:22:21,648 --> 01:22:27,802
I know this might be awkward,
but I want you to use this.

763
01:22:27,906 --> 01:22:30,930
God, Chad...

764
01:22:31,034 --> 01:22:36,248
This is Miles Davis
and John Coltrane.

765
01:22:36,456 --> 01:22:39,480
Stockholm 1963.

766
01:22:39,689 --> 01:22:44,694
Two masters of freedom, playing
before their art was corrupted -

767
01:22:44,903 --> 01:22:54,288
- by cocktail-lounge performers
who destroyed this American legacy.

768
01:22:54,392 --> 01:22:56,895
Jazz.

769
01:22:58,459 --> 01:23:02,630
I've put some Mingus
on there, too.

770
01:23:08,574 --> 01:23:13,788
- No barriers, no boundaries...
- Chad, I got it.

771
01:24:07,178 --> 01:24:12,913
You know
this is gonna change everything.

772
01:24:13,017 --> 01:24:16,668
Promise?

773
01:24:21,569 --> 01:24:25,739
What is this muslc?

774
01:24:58,482 --> 01:25:04,218
I love getting up in the morning
and beginning another great day!

775
01:25:07,138 --> 01:25:13,081
Great!
Did you really need to do this?

776
01:25:24,135 --> 01:25:31,122
- I'm getting him up, don't worry.
- What? I'm just waiting for coffee.

777
01:25:31,330 --> 01:25:35,709
- Just tell me one thing.
- No.

778
01:25:37,274 --> 01:25:44,157
I'm worried this guy may not have
an emotional marble in his head.

779
01:25:44,365 --> 01:25:50,309
Laurel, if I start talking . ..
I took a chance, all right?

780
01:25:50,413 --> 01:25:55,835
- This guy's on the bottom rung.
- Maybe I am taking advantage.

781
01:25:56,044 --> 01:25:59,485
Does that make me a bad person?

782
01:25:59,694 --> 01:26:05,429
Roger was popular and charming,
and not so nice to me, and he died.

783
01:26:05,638 --> 01:26:12,519
Why should I let this guy go when
my body tells me that he's the one?

784
01:26:12,728 --> 01:26:19,402
- I just wanted the fun details.
- Why didn't you say so?

785
01:26:19,611 --> 01:26:26,493
Well, you might be interested
in this one little detail...

786
01:26:28,161 --> 01:26:31,603
I love him.

787
01:26:31,707 --> 01:26:36,086
I do! I love him,
and I don't care what you think.

788
01:26:36,295 --> 01:26:42,865
I love him for the man he wants
to be, and for the man he almost is.

789
01:26:42,969 --> 01:26:48,183
I love him, Laurel. I love him.

790
01:26:48,287 --> 01:26:51,207
Hi, Jerry.

791
01:26:52,562 --> 01:26:56,108
Act natural.

792
01:26:59,757 --> 01:27:05,493
- Tell me he's not there.
- He's not there.

793
01:27:05,701 --> 01:27:09,143
- Easy, ladies.
- Coffee, Jerry?

794
01:27:09,351 --> 01:27:14,670
No, thanks. We bottom feeders
prefer cereal first.

795
01:27:14,878 --> 01:27:19,153
- Let's have Apple Jacks.
- Apple Jacks it is.

796
01:27:19,362 --> 01:27:23,533
Dorothy... good morning, darling.

797
01:27:26,244 --> 01:27:29,476
- Good morning.
- What's going on?

798
01:27:29,685 --> 01:27:36,151
A lot. We've got a big fax.
We need this commission.

799
01:27:36,359 --> 01:27:40,217
Milk? Cheers.

800
01:27:48,038 --> 01:27:51,897
That was really great of you,
this morning.

801
01:27:52,105 --> 01:27:59,822
Let's just root for a big offer
so we can move into a real office.

802
01:28:00,030 --> 01:28:04,097
Would you mind? Thanks a lot.

803
01:28:11,396 --> 01:28:13,795
Shit!

804
01:28:18,070 --> 01:28:22,762
1.7 for three years?
We owe more than that!

805
01:28:22,971 --> 01:28:28,811
- I'll get back to them.
- They're fucking us in the ass!

806
01:28:29,020 --> 01:28:32,669
I'm sorry,
I'm a little pregnant right now.

807
01:28:32,877 --> 01:28:38,821
- I feel like crying, Jerry.
- Don't take this so emotionally.

808
01:28:38,925 --> 01:28:43,097
- We'll roll with the problem.
- Why are you so calm?

809
01:28:43,305 --> 01:28:50,813
"Don't take it emotionally?"
You need to get emotional.

810
01:28:50,918 --> 01:28:54,985
- Get me Bob Sugar on the phone.
- Marcee...

811
01:28:56,444 --> 01:29:01,345
- You want to leave me?
- What exactly do you stand for?

812
01:29:01,450 --> 01:29:05,621
- What do you stand for?
- How about integrity?

813
01:29:05,830 --> 01:29:11,356
There's so much greed in the world
I don't know what to tell my son!

814
01:29:11,461 --> 01:29:15,944
But this guy isn't yelling,
"Show me the money!"

815
01:29:16,152 --> 01:29:20,949
Do you know he's broke
and working for you for free?

816
01:29:21,993 --> 01:29:25,642
Broke! Broke, broke, broke.

817
01:29:25,850 --> 01:29:31,481
- Sorry, I'm not so good at insults.
- That was pretty good.

818
01:29:33,671 --> 01:29:36,799
Let me show you something.

819
01:29:39,928 --> 01:29:45,142
- Here. Rod, read this.
- No, no, no...

820
01:29:45,350 --> 01:29:49,417
This is important, Jerry.

821
01:29:49,522 --> 01:29:54,214
- I appreciate this, but...
- You should be proud of that.

822
01:29:54,423 --> 01:30:01,304
Tell me what to do. Tell me to eat
lima beans, I'll eat lima beans.

823
01:30:02,452 --> 01:30:08,917
Tell me if this is the best
we can get... He's my agent.

824
01:30:09,021 --> 01:30:14,966
I'll tell you what you're gonna do.
Reject that shitty contract.

825
01:30:15,174 --> 01:30:20,701
Play out your existing contract,
and next year you're a free agent.

826
01:30:20,909 --> 01:30:26,749
Baby, this is us. You and me.
We determine our worth.

827
01:30:26,957 --> 01:30:33,527
You are a strong, proud,
surviving, splendid black man.

828
01:30:35,508 --> 01:30:40,513
Marcee... you are the shit.

829
01:30:47,813 --> 01:30:53,131
- If you get injured, you get zero.
- It won't happen.

830
01:30:54,173 --> 01:30:58,345
Rod, it's a risk.

831
01:30:58,553 --> 01:31:03,246
You bet on me, like I bet on you.

832
01:31:07,417 --> 01:31:11,171
You know?

833
01:31:14,091 --> 01:31:17,845
You know, baby?

834
01:31:17,949 --> 01:31:21,703
- You're so crazy .. .
- I love you, baby.

835
01:31:22,329 --> 01:31:27,543
- Let me kiss that head.
- Thank you.

836
01:31:33,903 --> 01:31:39,221
I'm taking that job in San Diego.
You can't afford me.

837
01:31:39,430 --> 01:31:44,958
- You can't afford me.
- I'll find something for Tidwell.

838
01:31:45,062 --> 01:31:48,920
- I refuse to be a drain.
- We'll stay afloat.

839
01:31:49,128 --> 01:31:53,612
We'll stay afloat. Don't leave.

840
01:31:53,821 --> 01:31:58,305
- Rod, get on the camel.
- You've been on my ass all day.

841
01:31:58,409 --> 01:32:01,746
- He's my client.
- Get him on the camel.

842
01:32:01,954 --> 01:32:06,543
- We don't need a camel.
- It's a Camel Chevrolet.

843
01:32:06,751 --> 01:32:11,339
- See? He's feeling my pain!
- Get on the camel.

844
01:32:11,443 --> 01:32:16,344
- I'm pulling him from this.
- Just get rid of the camel.

845
01:32:16,553 --> 01:32:21,454
- This isn't what I had in mind.
- Right, let's bounce.

846
01:32:23,435 --> 01:32:27,816
Pulling him?
You begged me to hire him.

847
01:32:28,441 --> 01:32:36,262
I know you needed that commission,
but this isn't exactly Reebok.

848
01:32:36,470 --> 01:32:41,684
- Can I ask you a personal question?
- Are we gonna be friends now?

849
01:32:41,788 --> 01:32:46,794
- Have you dated any single mothers?
- I was raised by a single mother.

850
01:32:47,002 --> 01:32:52,321
I think, after this, she's gonna
have to take that job in San Diego.

851
01:32:52,529 --> 01:32:56,909
First of all,
single mothers don't date.

852
01:32:57,118 --> 01:33:04,730
They've been to the puppet show
and they've seen the strings.

853
01:33:05,564 --> 01:33:10,361
Do you love her...?
Don't tell me you don't know.

854
01:33:10,569 --> 01:33:14,844
I don't want her to go.
We've been hanging out a lot.

855
01:33:14,948 --> 01:33:19,745
That's bullshit!
You've got to be fair to her.

856
01:33:19,954 --> 01:33:25,898
Single mothers are a sacred thing.
You've got to have the talk.

857
01:33:26,107 --> 01:33:32,363
She loves you. If you don't
love her, you've got to tell her.

858
01:33:34,240 --> 01:33:38,411
The kid's amazing. He...

859
01:33:40,184 --> 01:33:43,104
I feel you...

860
01:33:43,208 --> 01:33:48,318
But a real man wouldn't shoplift
the pooty from a single mother.

861
01:33:48,526 --> 01:33:54,053
I didn't shoplift the pooty.

862
01:33:57,285 --> 01:34:01,769
All right, I shoplifted the pooty.

863
01:34:10,528 --> 01:34:15,638
You know, John Coltrane
once said to Miles Davis...

864
01:34:15,742 --> 01:34:21,373
When you say goodbye to him, just
be cool. What's meant to be will be.

865
01:34:21,582 --> 01:34:27,109
You'll see each other. I'm losing
the only person who listens to me.

866
01:34:27,318 --> 01:34:30,967
- Seriously.
- You're doing the right thing.

867
01:34:31,071 --> 01:34:36,598
You need to start your life,
not cushion the fall for him.

868
01:34:40,039 --> 01:34:43,793
I'm almost sympathetic to the guy.

869
01:34:48,382 --> 01:34:51,823
Bye.

870
01:34:56,828 --> 01:35:02,042
Listen, you're gonna
like it in San Diego, Ray.

871
01:35:02,146 --> 01:35:04,753
Ray...

872
01:35:04,962 --> 01:35:09,550
It's gonna be great there.
You'll make a lot of friends.

873
01:35:09,655 --> 01:35:15,807
- I'll see you this weekend.
- Go ahead and go.

874
01:35:20,082 --> 01:35:23,628
Go ahead and go.

875
01:35:32,908 --> 01:35:37,392
- Are you okay to drive this?
- This rig? No problem.

876
01:35:37,600 --> 01:35:42,606
- I'll see you this weekend.
- Get in the car.

877
01:35:42,814 --> 01:35:47,716
I'll see you in a couple of days...
and I love you.

878
01:35:48,966 --> 01:35:53,555
I love you, too... What?

879
01:35:53,763 --> 01:35:57,204
- Nothing.
- I'll see you soon.

880
01:35:57,414 --> 01:36:02,105
Look, if this weekend
should turn into next month, -

881
01:36:02,314 --> 01:36:07,946
- and next month into whatever,
don't make a joke of your life.

882
01:36:08,050 --> 01:36:11,387
Go back and read what you wrote.

883
01:36:11,595 --> 01:36:17,018
You're better than the Bob Sugars.
Don't forget that.

884
01:36:34,119 --> 01:36:37,978
- Wait a second.
- No! Oh, God.

885
01:36:39,645 --> 01:36:44,547
- We can save on medical...
- Don't listen to him, Dorothy.

886
01:36:44,651 --> 01:36:49,865
What if we stay together?
What if we got married?

887
01:36:50,073 --> 01:36:55,496
- Would you stay?
- No, don't do that. Don't say that.

888
01:36:55,705 --> 01:36:59,250
Well... say it if you want to.

889
01:37:03,943 --> 01:37:07,905
Will you marry me?

890
01:37:11,972 --> 01:37:16,143
What are you thinking?

891
01:37:46,280 --> 01:37:51,702
Laurel! We're getting married.

892
01:37:51,911 --> 01:37:58,063
Do you, Jerry Magulre,
take this woman to be your wife?

893
01:37:58,375 --> 01:38:05,258
And do you, Dorothy Boyd,
take this man to be your husband?

894
01:38:06,092 --> 01:38:11,619
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

895
01:38:49,993 --> 01:38:52,913
I should go.

896
01:39:11,891 --> 01:39:14,915
We did it.

897
01:39:15,020 --> 01:39:19,087
We sure did.

898
01:39:36,396 --> 01:39:40,776
You fuck this up, I'll kill you.

899
01:39:45,678 --> 01:39:48,389
I'm glad we had this talk.

900
01:39:50,369 --> 01:39:54,124
Look at them.

901
01:39:54,228 --> 01:39:58,711
She is so beautiful.

902
01:40:13,311 --> 01:40:18,004
I don't believe they taped this.

903
01:40:23,947 --> 01:40:29,057
I'm gonna release this to ESPN.

904
01:40:29,161 --> 01:40:35,313
- You think I'm joking.
- No, but I know where you live.

905
01:40:36,774 --> 01:40:41,466
You didn't have the talk, did you?

906
01:40:43,134 --> 01:40:45,533
No.

907
01:40:45,741 --> 01:40:50,225
Well, this definitely
was another way to go.

908
01:40:50,434 --> 01:40:55,022
Hey, Dorothy, come here.
Ladies and gentlemen...

909
01:40:55,126 --> 01:41:00,966
Mr. and Mrs. Maguire.
We're gonna have a great season.

910
01:41:09,829 --> 01:41:15,043
Hey, Scotty.
Tidwell did four for 36.

911
01:41:15,251 --> 01:41:19,944
- Jerry... he's having a good game.
- You bet he is.

912
01:41:20,048 --> 01:41:23,385
You're gonna miss him next year.

913
01:41:27,869 --> 01:41:31,727
I've got a great team behind me
and I'm loving it.

914
01:41:38,506 --> 01:41:44,449
- That's my mo-fo!
- Come here.

915
01:41:44,658 --> 01:41:51,436
Be the first man in the family not
to say that, and we'll let you live.

916
01:41:51,645 --> 01:41:54,669
Go kiss Daddy.

917
01:42:04,575 --> 01:42:09,164
I saw you limping a little,
after the first quarter...

918
01:42:11,875 --> 01:42:17,506
I twisted my ankle.

919
01:42:17,714 --> 01:42:22,093
That went well.
Anybody else worth talking to?

920
01:42:22,302 --> 01:42:24,700
Let's go.

921
01:42:25,952 --> 01:42:30,332
- How's your head?
- Terrible.

922
01:42:30,958 --> 01:42:36,693
How you doing, Rod? Tough game.

923
01:42:39,091 --> 01:42:45,347
That quarterback sucks.
He's gonna get me killed.

924
01:42:46,599 --> 01:42:53,377
My brains will be blown loose
before you get me my 10 million.

925
01:42:57,131 --> 01:43:02,867
You take care out on that field.
You're my entire client roster.

926
01:43:02,971 --> 01:43:07,454
- Go home to your wife.
- What's that supposed to mean?

927
01:43:07,559 --> 01:43:13,816
- What are you doing here?
- Giving you personal attention.

928
01:43:14,024 --> 01:43:17,256
- You don't want to go home.
- What?

929
01:43:17,361 --> 01:43:22,158
I'm just trying to talk to you.
How's your marriage?

930
01:43:22,366 --> 01:43:26,642
The husband and wife thing,
how is that?

931
01:43:32,690 --> 01:43:38,008
- Not everyone has what you have.
- Why did you get married?

932
01:43:38,216 --> 01:43:42,492
- I'm just asking as a friend.
- You want an answer?

933
01:43:42,701 --> 01:43:46,663
Loyalty... she was loyal.

934
01:43:51,147 --> 01:43:55,319
Everything... grew from there.

935
01:43:56,152 --> 01:44:00,741
It just... grew from there.

936
01:44:01,888 --> 01:44:06,580
- That's an answer?
- That's the answer.

937
01:44:06,789 --> 01:44:11,377
It's not sexy...
but that's an answer.

938
01:44:11,481 --> 01:44:17,842
"Tell him what he's won, Bob.
A beautiful marriage!" Shit!

939
01:44:18,050 --> 01:44:23,681
I'm happy to entertain you,
as always, Rod.

940
01:44:24,725 --> 01:44:30,773
I have a question for you.
Are we really friends?

941
01:44:30,981 --> 01:44:37,446
You know, friends can tell
each other anything, right?

942
01:44:37,654 --> 01:44:42,347
I'll tell you why you don't
have your $10 million.

943
01:44:42,555 --> 01:44:47,561
You play for the money. You play
with your head, not your heart.

944
01:44:47,769 --> 01:44:53,400
When you get on the field,
it's all about what you didn't get.

945
01:44:53,609 --> 01:44:59,449
Who's to blame. Who's got
the contract you didn't get.

946
01:44:59,553 --> 01:45:05,601
That is not what inspires people!

947
01:45:05,810 --> 01:45:09,146
Shut up!
Play the game from your heart.

948
01:45:09,355 --> 01:45:14,464
Then I'll show you the kwan.
And that's the truth!

949
01:45:14,673 --> 01:45:20,513
Can you handle it?
It's just a question from a friend.

950
01:45:20,722 --> 01:45:25,831
When they call you "shrimp",
I'm the one who defends you!

951
01:45:26,040 --> 01:45:31,358
I don't want to be friends no more.
And quit using that word kwan.

952
01:45:31,984 --> 01:45:35,424
- I'll see you in L.A.
- No heart?

953
01:45:35,529 --> 01:45:40,013
I'm all heart, motherfucker!

954
01:46:16,615 --> 01:46:23,601
- How many concussions has he had?
- I can't get no respect.

955
01:46:41,328 --> 01:46:46,125
I went to see this so-called
black film the other day.

956
01:46:46,334 --> 01:46:54,259
No more salt for you. The biggest
game of the season is coming up.

957
01:46:55,093 --> 01:47:01,350
20 minutes of coming attractions.
All black films and all violent.

958
01:47:01,558 --> 01:47:06,459
- Brothers shooting brothers .. .
- I hate you going out alone.

959
01:47:06,668 --> 01:47:12,299
- Oh, baby .. .
- My Pisces queen.

960
01:47:14,071 --> 01:47:18,451
I hate seeing movies without you.

961
01:47:18,555 --> 01:47:24,186
I won't do it anymore, okay?

962
01:47:31,382 --> 01:47:36,595
- Baby.
- Baby!

963
01:47:36,700 --> 01:47:40,245
- Now?
- Baby now!

964
01:47:41,080 --> 01:47:48,274
- Ray, it's time to go.
- Do you take Visa? Take it!

965
01:47:49,839 --> 01:47:57,347
What were you thinking tonight,
watching them go through that?

966
01:47:57,451 --> 01:48:04,333
I was thinking,
"I hope he doesn't get injured."

967
01:48:06,002 --> 01:48:11,528
Sometimes I can't tell at all what's
going on in that head of yours.

968
01:48:16,638 --> 01:48:23,311
- And I don't know your noises yet.
- Well, when you wonder, ask me.

969
01:48:23,415 --> 01:48:27,483
Okay, I will.

970
01:48:27,691 --> 01:48:32,905
I thought I just did.

971
01:48:34,991 --> 01:48:38,953
- Why do you love me?
- Why do you love me?

972
01:48:39,161 --> 01:48:44,584
- Jerry, can I come and watch TV?
- Just for a few minutes.

973
01:49:03,668 --> 01:49:08,255
- He's not going anywhere.
- I know.

974
01:49:08,359 --> 01:49:14,721
- Can we talk about somethlng else?
- No, I'm incapable of small talk.

975
01:49:14,929 --> 01:49:19,100
But that's why you love me, right?

976
01:49:30,571 --> 01:49:36,410
I'm about personal attention.
I'm available to you 24 hours a day.

977
01:49:36,619 --> 01:49:41,624
I'll be in Phoenix tomorrow
for Monday Night Football.

978
01:49:41,729 --> 01:49:47,776
I can be in Indiana
by 11:30 Tuesday morning.

979
01:49:47,985 --> 01:49:55,180
I don't need an answer now.
I'll call you tomorrow.

980
01:49:55,389 --> 01:50:01,020
All right, thank you, Marilee.

981
01:50:02,272 --> 01:50:06,755
Indiana, Tuesday.
I'll be there.

982
01:50:10,092 --> 01:50:14,680
- It's my fault.
- What?

983
01:50:15,202 --> 01:50:21,146
It's not fair to you,
this whole thing.

984
01:50:22,501 --> 01:50:27,923
Come here.
Tell me, let me help.

985
01:50:28,132 --> 01:50:33,764
I took advantage of you and
I did it with the help of a kid.

986
01:50:35,223 --> 01:50:40,333
I was just on some wild ride.
I thought...

987
01:50:40,437 --> 01:50:46,172
I thought I was in love enough
for both of us.

988
01:50:46,276 --> 01:50:53,889
I jumped at your proposal
when it was still just hypothetical.

989
01:50:54,932 --> 01:51:01,292
I did this, and at least
I can do something about it now.

990
01:51:01,501 --> 01:51:06,611
I'm not a guy who runs.
I stick.

991
01:51:08,488 --> 01:51:15,265
- I don't need you to stick.
- What do you want? My soul?

992
01:51:15,474 --> 01:51:21,417
- Why not? I deserve that.
- What if I'm not built that way?

993
01:51:23,503 --> 01:51:29,552
- I think we made a mistake.
- What if it's true?

994
01:51:29,761 --> 01:51:33,514
Great at friendship,
bad at intimacy.

995
01:51:33,723 --> 01:51:37,686
That's the theme
of my bachelor film.

996
01:51:37,790 --> 01:51:41,960
I know, I watched lt.
I know it by heart.

997
01:51:45,715 --> 01:51:50,615
- I don't like to give up.
- Please...

998
01:51:50,825 --> 01:51:55,933
My need to make the best of things,
and your need to be responsible ...

999
01:51:56,039 --> 01:52:01,878
If we don't do something now, we
could lose ten years being polite.

1000
01:52:04,902 --> 01:52:10,533
Let's just call this next road trip
what it really is:

1001
01:52:10,741 --> 01:52:14,704
A nice long break.

1002
01:52:21,378 --> 01:52:24,610
What about Ray?

1003
01:52:27,113 --> 01:52:30,867
Well, you'll be friends.

1004
01:52:30,972 --> 01:52:34,621
- Friends?
- Yes.

1005
01:52:36,811 --> 01:52:44,111
- Of course you'll be friends.
- I'll take him to the zoo.

1006
01:52:45,570 --> 01:52:54,120
- So this break is a breakup.
- Come on, this isn't easy for me.

1007
01:52:54,329 --> 01:52:58,084
On the surface
everything looks fine.

1008
01:52:58,292 --> 01:53:05,592
I've got this great guy,
and he loves my kid.

1009
01:53:07,259 --> 01:53:10,389
And he sure does like me a lot.

1010
01:53:16,541 --> 01:53:20,399
And I can't live like that.

1011
01:53:22,067 --> 01:53:25,404
It's not how I'm built.

1012
01:53:57,730 --> 01:54:02,735
If this is empty,
this doesn't matter.

1013
01:54:24,529 --> 01:54:28,805
It was just a mission statement.

1014
01:54:59,672 --> 01:55:03,842
Hey, Rod, how are you doing?
How's it going?

1015
01:55:04,051 --> 01:55:06,345
Go.

1016
01:55:08,326 --> 01:55:12,184
- Where's your agent?
- I don't know.

1017
01:55:12,393 --> 01:55:17,190
You belong with the big boys.
You belong with the big money.

1018
01:55:17,294 --> 01:55:21,257
- You're Rod Tidwell!
- Get away from my guy.

1019
01:55:21,465 --> 01:55:26,054
- I was just handling it.
- Just go. Flee.

1020
01:55:26,262 --> 01:55:32,414
This is a nice moment for you.
I'm gonna let you have it.

1021
01:55:32,623 --> 01:55:37,003
Give me a call, Rod.
Say hi to Marcee.

1022
01:55:43,155 --> 01:55:48,786
- Thanks for coming.
- I missed you.

1023
01:55:48,890 --> 01:55:52,749
What can I say?
You're all I've got.

1024
01:55:55,043 --> 01:56:00,466
This is Frank Gifford in Tempe,
Arizona's Sun Devil Stadium.

1025
01:56:00,570 --> 01:56:05,784
The Cardinals are still alive
for a play-off spot.

1026
01:56:05,992 --> 01:56:12,248
The reason for that is the
outstandlng play of Rod Tidwell.

1027
01:56:12,457 --> 01:56:18,505
The Dallas Cowboys are on a roll.
They know they're in the play-offs.

1028
01:56:18,609 --> 01:56:23,302
If Arizona wins tonight
and next week, -

1029
01:56:23,510 --> 01:56:29,350
- they'll make the play-offs
for the flrst time in 21 years.

1030
01:56:29,558 --> 01:56:33,208
You'd better not mess up tonight.

1031
01:56:33,417 --> 01:56:37,901
What did I say? He's always
nervous for televised games.

1032
01:56:38,005 --> 01:56:43,115
The Cowboys contlnue their mlssion
on Monday Night Football.

1033
01:56:50,518 --> 01:56:55,628
Hey, Shannon.
Great column this morning.

1034
01:57:10,331 --> 01:57:12,730
What a bruiser.

1035
01:57:12,834 --> 01:57:20,134
The Cardinals just refuse to go
quietly into the desert night.

1036
01:57:20,238 --> 01:57:24,825
I'm just trying
to be a little poetic.

1037
01:57:26,286 --> 01:57:30,144
A tough hit on Tidwell.

1038
01:57:30,352 --> 01:57:36,088
- I'd have made a touchdown.
- That's his sixth catch tonlght.

1039
01:57:36,297 --> 01:57:40,467
A first down
at the 19 yard line.

1040
01:57:40,676 --> 01:57:48,184
- Another savage hit on Tidwell.
- They're really working Tidwell.

1041
01:57:48,288 --> 01:57:54,754
- What does Daddy always say?
- It looks worse than it is.

1042
01:57:54,962 --> 01:57:59,758
- He's gonna kill himself.
- Will you be quiet!

1043
01:57:59,864 --> 01:58:03,617
Two minutes to play.
Dallas leading by three.

1044
01:58:03,826 --> 01:58:07,893
Second down and one,
at the Dallas 11 yard line.

1045
01:58:10,186 --> 01:58:14,149
Down he goes for a slx yard loss.

1046
01:58:14,879 --> 01:58:17,277
Good move.

1047
01:58:17,486 --> 01:58:21,449
Swenson had too many men
in that pattern.

1048
01:58:24,160 --> 01:58:29,166
90 razor,
X-out on one, ready?

1049
01:58:31,667 --> 01:58:34,692
They had a chance there.

1050
01:58:34,901 --> 01:58:39,592
But from second and one
they've gone to third and seven.

1051
01:58:39,802 --> 01:58:43,451
Dallas 17, Arizona 14.

1052
01:58:43,660 --> 01:58:49,082
Tidwell in motion.
Moving back to his left.

1053
01:58:49,291 --> 01:58:55,652
Swenson puts one into the endzone.
Tidwell Touchdown Cardinals!

1054
01:58:55,756 --> 01:59:01,075
Tidwell held onto the football,
but he's still down on the ground.

1055
01:59:01,283 --> 01:59:06,601
He hit the ground hard, but managed
to maintain control of the football.

1056
01:59:06,810 --> 01:59:11,084
- He's hurt, too.
- He's not getting up.

1057
01:59:11,293 --> 01:59:16,090
- Look at the players' faces.
- Get up, baby.

1058
01:59:16,298 --> 01:59:23,702
The trainer ls on the field. It was
Tidwell's ninth catch of the night.

1059
01:59:33,192 --> 01:59:37,675
Can you hear me, Rod?

1060
01:59:44,245 --> 01:59:47,999
Commercial! Show me what's wrong
with my husband.

1061
01:59:48,103 --> 01:59:51,441
I told you he was
too small for the NFL.

1062
01:59:51,545 --> 01:59:56,549
- I'm just stating the truth.
- Tee Pee, shut up!

1063
01:59:56,759 --> 02:00:01,763
Can't you be loyal to your brother?
Get the hell out of my house!

1064
02:00:02,494 --> 02:00:05,935
Hello? Hold on.
It's Jerry Maguire.

1065
02:00:06,769 --> 02:00:09,271
Punk!

1066
02:00:10,523 --> 02:00:16,780
- Jerry, I am freaking out.
- Marcee, he's unconscious.

1067
02:00:16,988 --> 02:00:21,368
Just stay calm.
I'll call you back.

1068
02:00:21,577 --> 02:00:24,496
There are good doctors here.

1069
02:00:24,705 --> 02:00:31,379
- I cannot stay calm.
- Stay calm.

1070
02:00:31,587 --> 02:00:34,507
Your family needs you to stay calm.

1071
02:00:34,716 --> 02:00:41,493
My whole life is this family,
and it does not work without him!

1072
02:00:41,702 --> 02:00:48,584
All eyes here at Sun Devil Stadium
are focused on Rod Tidwell.

1073
02:00:48,793 --> 02:00:54,424
Just do whatever you can
to get Rod to me.

1074
02:00:54,528 --> 02:00:58,491
Do whatever you can.
Please, Jerry.

1075
02:00:58,699 --> 02:01:04,226
At a time like thls, you just hope
his familly is not watching this.

1076
02:01:04,851 --> 02:01:08,815
It could be his neck.
It could be his back.

1077
02:01:12,672 --> 02:01:15,696
Blink! Wake up!

1078
02:01:28,523 --> 02:01:32,172
Rod! Can you hear me?

1079
02:01:32,381 --> 02:01:37,177
Can you hear me?
Do you know where you are?

1080
02:01:37,386 --> 02:01:41,557
The trainer is still trying
to revive Tidwell.

1081
02:01:42,704 --> 02:01:46,250
- Rod...?
- Let's get him off the field.

1082
02:01:46,354 --> 02:01:49,483
- No...
- Get him off the field.

1083
02:01:49,587 --> 02:01:54,280
Wait, wait...
Let me enjoy this for a minute.

1084
02:01:54,488 --> 02:01:59,910
We're looking for some movement.
Is that his head coming up?

1085
02:02:00,015 --> 02:02:04,707
He's trying to get up.
He is getting up.

1086
02:02:20,245 --> 02:02:25,145
- The whole stadium is standing.
- He's up on his feet.

1087
02:02:54,239 --> 02:03:00,496
Here's a guy who's normally
very truculent with the media.

1088
02:03:15,615 --> 02:03:20,934
Rod, we're happy for you, buddy.

1089
02:03:36,471 --> 02:03:40,538
- Congratulations, Jerry.
- Thank you.

1090
02:03:40,747 --> 02:03:43,875
Congratulations.

1091
02:03:45,440 --> 02:03:49,402
Jerry... Maguire!

1092
02:03:53,051 --> 02:03:56,076
I know.

1093
02:04:15,784 --> 02:04:18,391
Where's Jerry?

1094
02:04:37,891 --> 02:04:42,271
- We did it.
- You did it.

1095
02:04:43,627 --> 02:04:47,485
Why don't we have
that kind of relationship?

1096
02:04:55,305 --> 02:04:58,955
Is that your phone or mine?

1097
02:05:00,832 --> 02:05:03,648
Dorothy?

1098
02:05:03,752 --> 02:05:07,401
Marcee... No, he's right here.

1099
02:05:13,033 --> 02:05:17,725
We did it. I love you so much!

1100
02:05:21,896 --> 02:05:25,233
I love you!

1101
02:05:29,196 --> 02:05:35,556
I love you, Tyson.
How's the baby?

1102
02:05:52,136 --> 02:05:57,559
The problem is, like you
were saying, the biorhythms.

1103
02:05:57,663 --> 02:06:06,215
The neural pathways are set,
so it's hard for people to change.

1104
02:06:10,177 --> 02:06:17,059
I'm sorry, these stupid holidays
are making me feel more divorced.

1105
02:06:17,059 --> 02:06:20,188
The songs, the chocolate...

1106
02:06:36,038 --> 02:06:39,687
I have a confession to make.

1107
02:06:39,791 --> 02:06:47,300
I've listened to you all
tell a thousand sob-stories.

1108
02:06:47,404 --> 02:06:53,765
Maybe you're all correct.
Men are the enemy.

1109
02:06:53,974 --> 02:06:59,188
But I still love the enemy.

1110
02:07:12,952 --> 02:07:16,602
Hello.

1111
02:07:16,810 --> 02:07:20,773
I'm looking for my wife.

1112
02:07:31,514 --> 02:07:34,954
Wait...

1113
02:07:43,088 --> 02:07:48,615
If this is where it has to happen,
then this is where it has to happen.

1114
02:07:48,719 --> 02:07:54,454
I'm not letting you get rid of me.
How about that?

1115
02:07:59,251 --> 02:08:05,299
This used to be my specialty.
I was good in a living room.

1116
02:08:05,821 --> 02:08:09,575
And now, I just...

1117
02:08:21,149 --> 02:08:29,596
Tonight... our little company
had a very big night.

1118
02:08:29,701 --> 02:08:34,080
A very, very big night.

1119
02:08:36,687 --> 02:08:40,858
But it wasn't complete.

1120
02:08:40,962 --> 02:08:47,427
It wasn't nearly close
to being complete.

1121
02:08:47,531 --> 02:08:51,807
I couldn't share it with you.

1122
02:08:51,911 --> 02:08:55,040
I couldn't hear your voice.

1123
02:08:55,875 --> 02:08:58,898
I couldn't laugh about it with you.

1124
02:09:00,566 --> 02:09:04,112
I missed my... I missed my wife.

1125
02:09:20,275 --> 02:09:26,115
We live in a cynical world.

1126
02:09:26,219 --> 02:09:31,329
And we work in a business
of tough competitors.

1127
02:09:40,400 --> 02:09:47,492
I love you. You... complete me.

1128
02:09:48,847 --> 02:09:54,479
- And I just...
- Shut up!

1129
02:09:54,583 --> 02:10:01,360
You had me at "hello".

1130
02:10:12,518 --> 02:10:15,960
What a great discussion group.

1131
02:10:16,168 --> 02:10:20,651
Your father leaves home
on Christmas Eve.

1132
02:10:20,861 --> 02:10:25,344
Your mother had to sweep up
to pay your tuition.

1133
02:10:25,448 --> 02:10:32,852
Your brother lost a leg.
You've had a pretty horrific life.

1134
02:10:33,061 --> 02:10:38,796
- I'm not gonna cry, Roy.
- Well, I've got some good news.

1135
02:10:38,900 --> 02:10:44,845
I've got a contract here from the
Arizona Cardinals. Four years.

1136
02:10:45,053 --> 02:10:51,309
$11.2 million and you'll get
to play in your home state.

1137
02:10:51,518 --> 02:10:55,376
What do think of that?

1138
02:11:11,957 --> 02:11:17,275
I love everybody.
I love my wife! Marcee!

1139
02:11:18,526 --> 02:11:22,385
I love my kids.
Tyson and my new baby.

1140
02:11:22,593 --> 02:11:28,120
My older brother and
my younger brother Tee Pee.

1141
02:11:28,328 --> 02:11:31,873
You're militant, but I love you.

1142
02:11:31,977 --> 02:11:37,817
- I love my teammates.
- We only have a half-hour show.

1143
02:11:38,964 --> 02:11:45,951
Jerry... Congratulations.
Good for you.

1144
02:11:46,160 --> 02:11:51,374
- Hi, Jerry, you remember Troy.
- Yeah, we met in '93.

1145
02:11:51,478 --> 02:11:54,502
I enjoyed your memo.

1146
02:11:54,710 --> 02:11:59,716
- The Cardinals finally came around.
- We're out of time.

1147
02:11:59,820 --> 02:12:03,469
Wait, I'm forgetting somebody.

1148
02:12:03,678 --> 02:12:08,162
Jerry Maguire, my agent.

1149
02:12:11,082 --> 02:12:15,462
You are my ambassador
of kwan, man.

1150
02:12:15,566 --> 02:12:20,049
Rod, thank you...
We'll be right back.

1151
02:12:23,804 --> 02:12:28,497
- How did you like the zoo, buddy?
- It was great!

1152
02:12:33,919 --> 02:12:38,819
Hey, kid, throw the ball.

1153
02:12:50,812 --> 02:12:55,921
- Did you see?
- Oh, no... Let's go.

1154
02:12:56,130 --> 02:13:01,448
What? He won't make
the major leagues tomorrow.

1155
02:13:01,656 --> 02:13:09,165
But you can see he's got talent
and I know the right people...

1156
02:13:22,199 --> 02:13:25,536
I don't have all the answers.

1157
02:13:25,745 --> 02:13:30,542
In life, I've failed
as much as I've succeeded.

1158
02:13:30,750 --> 02:13:37,633
But I love my wife, I love life,
and I wish you my kind of success.

